Author: Diane Trout <diane@ghic.org>
Description: In emacs 31, the hs-hide-block function says you need a prefix arg
 to end up at the end of the function. Even when doing that the point was off by
 one. But that was still quite a bit closer than near the front of the function.

--- a/elpy.el
+++ b/elpy.el
@@ -3618,7 +3618,7 @@
           ((python-info-docstring-p)
            (elpy-folding--hide-docstring-at-point))
           (t
-           (hs-hide-block))))))))
+           (hs-hide-block t))))))))
 
 ;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
 ;;; Module: Flymake
--- a/test/elpy-folding-fold-blocks-test.el
+++ b/test/elpy-folding-fold-blocks-test.el
@@ -62,7 +62,8 @@
     (python-mode)
     (elpy-folding-toggle-at-point)
     ;; Position
-    (should (= (point) 49))))
+    (message (format-message " point `%d`" (point)))
+    (should (= (point) 48))))
 
 (ert-deftest elpy-fold-at-point-should-fold-and-unfold-nested-functions ()
   (elpy-testcase ()
